# Docs Conventions

## Ordering

Files in `docs/` use numeric prefixes: `00-*`, `01-*`, `02-*`, etc.

## Conflict resolution

If two docs describe the same thing differently, **the higher prefix wins**.

Example: `03-final-yoni-specs.md` overrides `01-yoni-language-spec.md`.

## Adding docs

New docs follow the same prefix pattern. Increment the prefix for new authoritative specs.

## Key doc map

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `00-initial.md` | Doc ordering rules |
| `01-yoni-language-spec.md` | Repo structure, linter, VS Code plan |
| `02-how-yoni-differes.md` | Why compiler/validator matters |
| `03-final-yoni-specs.md` | AST schemas, graph, repair, execution plan |
| `04-languages-while-building.md` | Language choices for compiler vs AI layer |
| `05-code-generation-mechanism.md` | Incremental generation: planner, jobs, manifest, context |
| `MANDATORY.md` | Core Yoni philosophy and block glossary |
